properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 31 at 12:41PM PST until February 2 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Hanford CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 45 mph
expected.

* WHERE...The Central and Southern San Joaquin Valley north of
Bakersfield, and West Side Hills.

* WHEN...From noon to 10 PM PST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree
limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
Travel may be difficult, particularly for high profile vehicles.
Blowing dust may reduce visibilities in some locations.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Highways affected include, but are not
limited to Highway 33, Highway 41, Highway 46, Highway 152
through Pacheco Pass, Highway 198, and Interstate 5.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM NOON TO 10 PM PST SUNDAY
